name: The Working Artisans' Club  Limited-Edition T-Shirt
description: Limited-edition Working Artisans' Club pocket t-shirt. 100% organic cotton. The Working Artisans’ Club is a celebration of modern-day makers. They shape boards, sew wetsuits and hand-make beautiful objects inspired by their passion for the outdoors. And they make life better for us all.

name: HUCK Subscription Radness
description:
Buy a special HUCK subs pack and you'll get six issues of HUCK delivered to your door for only £22*!

All subscribers will receive a customised HUCK letraset - complete with HUCK fonts, logos and other cool shit.

You can either treat yourself or give it as a gift to a friend.

If you'd like to give it as a gift, don't forget to include their name, address and email in the 'Note to Seller' on PayPal.

*Free postage for UK / £23.00 postage for Europe / £38.00 postage for Rest of the World.

name: HUCK magazine issue #041
description: The Documentary Photography Special Photo stories from the most talented names in documentary photography that are sure to challenge your perspective. Featuring... Cheryl Dunn, J.Grant Brittain, Guy Martin, Bryan Derballa, JM Lopez, Paul Calver, Laura Pannack, Charlie Shoemaker, Mustafah Abdulaziz, Elizabeth Dalziel, Shane McCauley, Spencer Murphy, Mike Belleme, Joni Sternbach, Alex Welsh, Alana Paterson, James Bowden and more... PLUS: - Olivier Laurent: The deputy editor of the British Journal of Photography explores how social media is empowering documentarians to bring down the wall between their audience and their work. - Geoff Dyer: The culture pundit expands on The Ongoing Moment – an acclaimed essay on the history of photography – and makes it relevant to a generation obsessed with documenting their own lives. - J. Malcolm Garcia: An exclusive piece of reportage from Kabul.

name: HUCK magazine issue #32
description: Huck x Thomas Campbell x Element present... The Flower Tote! To celebrate HUCK#032 with artist, photographer, filmmaker and surfer Thomas Campbell on the cover, we've created a cotton bag featuring Campbell’s beautiful artwork. The bag is free* with selected issues of HUCK (limited number available) and you can also find these special packs at select WH Smith; independent press shops; and selected surf, skate and snow shops. Inside the Issue... Thomas Campbell Not talking art with the renowned artist Swoon Talking art and activism with the street artist Muslim hip hop Meeting London's devout rappers Jamie Thomas The craft of Instagram Craftivist Collective Politcally minded sewing Plus... Berlin Tattoo Spoek Mathambo C.R. Stecyk III Vespas Roger Mihalko *Offer valid subject to stock availability
